<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: MONTEREY PARK; LANDLORD 
HELD IN SLAYING, BURNING OF VICTIM'S BODY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Monterey Park man was ordered held on $1-million bail Tuesday on a charge 
that he murdered a tenant, dismembered his body and tried to get rid of the 
parts by burning them and throwing them into a dumpster.  
</P>
<P>
 Arraignment for Peter Earl Burza, 41, was set for Nov. 15 in Alhambra 
Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 Burza was arrested Friday, when police arrived at his home and saw smoke 
rising from his chimney and smelled the pungent odor of burned flesh, said 
Deputy Dist. Atty. Stanley Williams. Police were tipped by gas station 
employees who said they had seen Burza throwing something into their trash bin 
earlier in the day. Williams said the victim, Craig Russel Kensinger, 42, had 
recently begun renting a room at Burza's Monterey Park home. 
</P>
