<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
D.A. OPENS INQUIRY INTO VOTER REGISTRATION FRAUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The district attorney's office announced Tuesday that it has opened a criminal 
investigation into allegations of voter registration fraud in Burbank, Pasadena 
and Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 District attorney's spokeswoman Sandi Gibbons said several people have been 
interviewed and that the investigation should be completed in two weeks.  
</P>
<P>
 The inquiry was started at the request of the County Board of Supervisors 
after Registrar-Recorder Bea Valdez confirmed several instances of voter fraud 
reported by the media. The fraud ranged from a dog being registered to 
discoveries that 11 people were improperly registered at one address. 
</P>
