<HEADLINE>
<P>
THEATER REVIEWS; A SPOOFY 'MURDER MYSTERY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.H. McCULLOH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Every year about this time, director Tony Reverditto of the Way Off Broadway 
Playhouse assembles a sort of boohaha to celebrate Halloween. This year's is 
called "The Way Off the Wall Murder Mystery." 
</P>
<P>
 And it is, as are all the company's comedy efforts, very off the wall. 
Reverditto, who wrote the script along with his cast, has gathered characters 
ludicrous and loony, most of them familiar to WOB audiences, such as intrepid 
and dribbling private eye Spit Phlegmster (David Walloch), Jan Tiehen's 
grimacing, gravel-voiced Leona Helmsley, and Reverditto's own Judge 
Cottonmouth, who usually loses not only the wads he is chewing but also, 
somewhere along the line, the cotton eyebrows he hides behind. 
</P>
<P>
 There are some unfamiliar faces, too: the silent and mysterious prelate Monk 
Fish (James LaFave); very funny and very young Adam Jaso as Munchkin-sounding, 
diapered, cigar-chomping Pip Squeek, and an amusing scrounge of a torn-jeaned 
and dog-collared Prosecutor (Steve Andreno). 
</P>
<P>
 What they're all doing is a sort of sendup of those "murder mystery weekends" 
so popular locally. The audience is seated in the Mystery Lounge, where 
chanteuse Veronica Bacall (Laura Spurlock) is murdered during a blackout. Or is 
she? Then, along with the above-mentioned suspects (and more), we are taken to 
the Mystery Funeral Home for the last rites and viewing. During intermission, 
the whole lot is arrested: Act 2 finds everyone in County Jail and County 
Courthouse, where, you're right, here come de judge. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 If it isn't anywhere near the Kids in the Hall, it does have some funny gags 
and a few good lines (and on opening night, some inadvertent goofs got laughs 
of their own). 
</P>
<P>
 Among the suspects is stand-up comic O.J. Pimpson (Godfrey Huguey) joking 
about you-know-what and wearing a T-shirt that says "Stay Alive on the 405!" 
But it's Halloween, and it's all in fun. 
</P>
<P>
 * "The Way Off the Wall Murder Mystery," the Way Off Broadway Playhouse, 1058 
E. 1st St., Santa Ana. Friday and Saturday, 8 p.m. Ends Saturday. $12. (714) 
547-8997. Running time: 1 hours, 50 minutes. David Walloch:Spit Phlegmster 
</P>
<P>
 Jan Tiehen:Leona Helmsley 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Jaso:Pip Squeek 
</P>
<P>
 Godfrey Huguey: O.J. Pimpson 
</P>
<P>
 Ron McCaw: Bulah Manly 
</P>
<P>
 James LaFave: Monk Fish 
</P>
<P>
 Laura Spurlock: Veronica Bacall 
</P>
<P>
 Tony Reverditto: Judge Cottonmouth 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Andreno: Prosecutor 
</P>
<P>
 A Way Off Broadway Playhouse production of a comedy written by the company and 
directed by Tony Reverditto. Scenic designs: David Walloch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Play Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110294-0038 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 094476 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
November 2, 1994, Wednesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part F; Page 2; Column 2; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
