<TEXT>
<P>
 Denver offensive coordinator Jim Fassel plans to change several audibles that 
quarterback John Elway uses at the line of scrimmage for Sunday's game against 
the Rams. 
</P>
<P>
 The reason? Ram backup quarterback Tommy Maddox knows the Broncos' offense, 
having backed up Elway for two seasons in Denver before being traded to the 
Rams in August. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Rookie Isaac Bruce, the sixth receiver taken in the draft, is second among 
rookie receivers in touchdowns with three, trailing only Cincinnati's Darnay 
Scott, who has four. 
