<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; USC; WHO'S ON FIRST IN RACE FOR ROSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rose Bowl race: 
</P>
<P>
 -- If USC wins the rest of its games and Oregon loses, the Trojans go to the 
Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 -- If Washington State wins the rest of its games and Arizona loses, the 
Cougars go to the Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 -- If Arizona wins the rest of its games and Oregon loses, the Wildcats go to 
the Rose Bowl.  
</P>
<P>
 -- If Oregon wins the rest of its games and Washington State loses, the Ducks 
go to the Rose Bowl.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Washington State Coach Mike Price, on Saturday's USC game: 
</P>
<P>
 "The USC game is one of the biggest games in my tenure here. The Arizona game 
was a big game, but there were still a lot of games left. . . . Beating USC is 
one of the things our seniors want to do more than anything. USC is one team 
they haven't knocked off yet." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 USC Coach John Robinson is worried about the team's depth at guard with Phalen 
Pounds sidelined because of a knee injury and Chris Brymer possibly sidelined 
because of an ankle sprain. "We'd get down to scout team players if we had to 
replace anyone else," Robinson said.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Washington State, which defeated UCLA in September, has never beaten UCLA and 
USC in the same season. . . . Linebacker Errick Herrin moved into second place 
on the USC tackles list. He had six against California and now has 50, trailing 
only leader Jeff Kopp, who has 65. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
