<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; UCLA; EDWARDS LEADS DEFENSIVE CORPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM HODGES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA linebacker Donnie Edwards leads the Bruins in almost every defensive 
category.He has 90 tackles, 15 more than any other UCLA defender. 
</P>
<P>
 His 11 1/2 sacks are one fewer than 1993 All-American Jamir Miller and 1 1/2 
off Carnell Lake's school record 13. 
</P>
<P>
 Edwards also has 20 tackles for losses, second in school history to the 22 of 
Marvcus Patton, and leads the team in interceptions with three. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 After missing six field goals in seven tries in four games, Bjorn Merten has 
made four of his last five tries. . . . Sharmon Shaw's 912 rushing yards are 
the most by a Bruin running back since Kevin Williams rushed for 1,141 in 1991. 
JIM HODGES 
</P>
