<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISH REPORT: LARGEMOUTH BASS ARE BEST OF LUNKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Catfish might be giving way to trout as the primary target of Southland 
anglers, but at Ventura County's Lake Casitas, largemouth bass still reign. 
</P>
<P>
 Several fish topped 10 pounds in the last week, with the biggest -- an 
11-pound 12-ounce fish -- landed by Robert Hefernam of Ojai. 
</P>
<P>
 Of course catfish still have some feeding to do at Casitas before settling 
down for the winter.  
</P>
<P>
 George Collier of Port Hueneme proved that by filling a stringer with seven 
fish totaling 90 pounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
