<P>
 Supermarket, Meat Industries Seek to Stop E. Coli Testing: The industries sued 
the U.S. Agriculture Department to halt government testing of the ground-beef 
supply for the rare but potentially deadly bacteria E. coli O157:H7. The 
lawsuit, filed in U.S. District Court in Austin, Tex., claims the testing, 
which began Oct. 17, would mislead consumers into believing any ground beef 
they bought would be free of pathogens. The plaintiffs did not ask for an 
immediate injunction, so it could be several weeks before U.S. District Judge 
James Nowlin acts. 
