<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michael Arkush and David Brady 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TICKET-FREE: Southwest Airlines has something new for passengers who don't 
have time to get tickets: a no-ticket system. Passengers can confirm their 
reservations by phone with a credit card and then can board their planes with 
just a confirmation number and picture I.D. . . . Southwest operates 48 flights 
daily in and out of Burbank Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 FIGHTING BACK: Speaking of tickets, wouldn't it be great if parking tickets 
also disappeared? Not a chance. Parking tickets are a part of life, and very 
few people bother to contest them (B2). . . . But John Romano of Chatsworth is. 
Romano got a ticket while helping his disabled wife out of the car a few weeks 
ago, and says that under the current system, "you are guilty until proven 
innocent." 
</P>
<P>
 MESSY BUSINESS: Mirk Mirkin, above, is a major mess. Or, at least, his office 
is. The Sherman Oaks marketing and meeting planner recently won an honorable 
mention from Home Office Computing magazine in a contest seeking the messiest 
home office in America. . . . Mirkin, 67, who keeps papers, boxes and files 
everywhere, tries to keep tidy "but it catches up on me when the mail comes." 
</P>
<P>
 VALLEY GIRLS: It's a movie about a bunch named Brady . . . but don't look for 
Valley natives Eve Plumb and Maureen McCormick. Although many of the TV actors 
make cameo appearances in the Paramount production due out next year, the Brady 
Bunch's original Jan and Marcia both turned down parts. . . . Much of the 
picture was shot at Valley locations (F1). 
</P>
<P>
 GOING PUBLIC: The ax is poised over CSUN athletics. The only question is: 
Where will it fall? On Tuesday, administrators said they'll ask the public to 
help them make that decision (C8). . . . The cuts became likely after students 
voted last month against a $49 semester fee that would have generated $2.25 
million for the athletic department. 
</P>
