<P>
HALLOWEEN PRANKSTER DARKENS STORMY NIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teen-ager who was tossing eggs as a Halloween prank unwittingly created a 
fireball that knocked out electricity for at least 8,000 people. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the 15-year-old boy tossed one or two eggs over a fence at a 
Pennsylvania Electric Co. substation Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The combination of splattered egg and rain made the 34,000-watt transformers 
arc, creating a flash that was visible in most of Franklin. One witness 
reported seeing a fireball. The boy turned himself in and was treated at a 
hospital for ringing ears. 
</P>
