<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: DOWNEY; PARADE 
ORGANIZERS STRUGGLE TO RAISE FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Organizers of the annual Holiday Lane Parade are struggling to raise money. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chamber of Commerce, which sponsors the parade, has raised only one-third 
of the $27,000 needed to pay for the event. The 43rd annual parade will take 
place as planned Dec. 4, but officials say it may be the last one if they can't 
break even. Parade chairman Michael J. Prokop attributed the financial problems 
to lack of donations from businesses and a city decision to charge organizers 
for police patrols and other services, such as setting up bleachers. About 42 
of the city's 2,500 businesses have donated this year, Prokop said. 
</P>
