<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; AIRPORT GETS GRANT TO SOUNDPROOF SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Federal Aviation Administration has awarded $3 million to Burbank Airport 
to soundproof two schools. 
</P>
<P>
 The FAA grant will be coupled with $722,546 from the Burbank Airport Authority 
to soundproof St. Patrick's School in North Hollywood and Mingay Adult School 
in Burbank. Both schools are about one mile from the airport. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is scheduled to take at least two years, said Victor Gill, 
spokesman for the airport. 
</P>
<P>
 The soundproofing project is the result of an acoustical assessment done in 
1989, after which the FAA and airport allotted a total of $10 million to 
sound-insulate neighboring schools. MAKI BECKER 
