<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREASE FIRE CLOSES MALL EATERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Smoke from a small grease fire at the Glendale Galleria temporarily shut down 
the mall's food court on Tuesday afternoon and caused an estimated $200,000 in 
damage, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 "There were some flames and a lot of black smoke," said Officer Brian Cohen of 
the Glendale Police Department's substation in the mall on Central Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 "By the time it was all over, the food couldn't be re-served and it was closed 
down." 
</P>
<P>
 The 3 p.m. fire started in the ventilation system over a stove top at the 
Wazwan Restaurant, which features Indian cuisine. About a dozen firefighters 
put out the flames in 15 minutes, a Glendale fire dispatcher said. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no injuries, but about 100 customers were evacuated from the food 
court's 13 eateries and some adjacent stores. "The smoke is what caused us to 
evacuate the food court," said Melissa Beissner, spokeswoman for the mall. 
</P>
<P>
 About 20 stores were closed until 4:30 p.m., she said. The food court is 
expected to reopen today.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
