<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; HOUSE FIRE DESTROYS $550,000 IN ARTWORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire destroyed $550,000 worth of art in Ojai on Tuesday morning, county 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no injuries in the fire, which also caused $75,000 in damage to the 
house on San Gabriel Street, said Pam Sears, a county fire spokeswoman. 
Firefighter Mike Middough said an electrical short caused the fire about 8 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Middough said the damaged art included paintings and sculptures. 
</P>
<P>
 "They were burned completely," Middough said. "All it was was charred picture 
frames on the walls." 
</P>
<P>
 The home and the art were owned by Leonard and Linda Kiore, who own an Ojai 
wine and cheese store, officials said. IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</TEXT>
