<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY: BELL CANYON; FIREFIGHTERS PLAN CONTROLLED BURN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Firefighters will conduct a controlled burn of vegetation in the Santa Monica 
Mountains on Thursday to thin out tinder-dry growth, officials said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The burn will begin at 5 a.m. on 700 acres near Bell Canyon, county fire 
officials said. Residents of Bell Canyon, Agoura Hills, Hidden Hills, Las 
Virgenes Canyon and Liberty Canyon may notice smoke from the exercise, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire officials expect most of the smoke to loft high over populated areas. 
</P>
<P>
 The burn is needed to eliminate dry grass, officials said. That particular 
area has not burned in more than 10 years, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The burn will be canceled if windy or other unfavorable weather conditions 
develop, fire authorities said. KAY SAILLANT 
