<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: IRVINE; EXECUTIVE-SEARCH FIRM SEEKS PUBLIC'S INPUT IN 
SELECTING SCHOOL SUPERINTENDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSS LOAR 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What are residents looking for in the next leader of the Irvine Unified School 
District? That's the question an executive search firm will be asking Irvine 
residents in a series of half-hour interviews that begin today and end at noon 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The 17,500-student school district is inviting all community members to take 
part.In addition to the half-hour group interviews, a public forum is scheduled 
at 7 p.m. Thursday, at Woodbridge High School. 
</P>
<P>
 The interviews will be conducted by Management Analysis and Planning 
Associates, a Berkeley-based firm hired to develop a profile of the qualities 
community members want in a new superintendent. The firm also will survey 
community attitudes about the district. 
</P>
<P>
 David E. Brown, hired in 1987 to succeed A. Stanley Corey, spent a final 
morning at his district office Monday. He resigned to become superintendent of 
the Napa Valley Unified School District. Deputy Supt. Dean Waldfogel, one of 
three deputy superintendents in the district, is serving as interim 
superintendent. Waldfogel has said he is not a candidate.  
</P>
<P>
 Interview appointments may be scheduled by calling Donna Wilkerson at (714) 
651-0444, Ext. 201. Comments may be submitted in writing to Harry Weinberg at 
fax number (714) 559-9051.RUSS LOAR 
</P>
