<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the turn of the century, Orange County was home to several popular health 
spas and resorts. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the more famous was a weight-loss compound in the hills above Newport 
Beach.The resort was advertised in newspapers and attracted many dieters, 
especially from the East Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 A sliver of the San Joaquin Hills near Corona del Mar was named Anti-Fat 
Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa was home to a resort that featured several warm-water artesian 
wells for swimming. 
</P>
<P>
 Another popular swimming spot was the San Juan Hot Springs north of San Juan 
Capistrano. Today 
</P>
<P>
 A proposed bridge over the Santa Ana River that would link Newport Beach and 
Huntington Beach neighborhoods is the subject of a discussion sponsored by 
Speak Up Newport. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum will feature several panelists, including Newport Beach Public Works 
Director Don Webb, who will give a presentation on the proposed river crossing 
as well as several other projects. The discussion will be at 5:30 p.m. at Villa 
Nova restaurant, 3131 W. Coast Highway, Newport Beach. Information: (714) 
542-4226. 
</P>
