<P>
 Silicon Systems Moving Some Workers Out of Orange County: The Tustin-based 
company, which makes computer circuits, confirmed that it is moving its 
manufacturing operations.The privately held company, a subsidiary of 
Tokyo-based TDK Corp., said it will keep its corporate headquarters, main 
design center and about 800 of its employees in Tustin. It will move its 
remaining 150 manufacturing workers to a new plant, to be built at a site not 
yet chosen. Silicon Systems employs about 2,000 people worldwide, mostly in 
Tustin, Santa Cruz and Singapore. The company said it is considering locations 
in Oregon, Nevada and the Sacramento area. 
