<P>
POLITICAL SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 6 days to go before Californians go to the polls 
</P>
<P>
 THE GOVERNOR'S RACE 
</P>
<P>
 * What Happened Tuesday: Democrat Kathleen Brown held a rally in San 
Bernardino, where she was accompanied by Vice President Al Gore, and then made 
stops in Santa Barbara, San Luis Obispo, Santa Maria and Oxnard. She blasted 
Gov. Pete Wilson as a bully for his support of Proposition 187, the 
anti-illegal immigration initiative. Wilson held a "law enforcement bus tour" 
with stops in Riverside, Los Angeles, Garden Grove and San Diego, where he 
hammered Brown as a "no-show" on past efforts to strengthen criminal penalties. 
</P>
<P>
 * What's Ahead: Brown was scheduled to set off on a 29-hour bus and plane tour 
of California that will take her from Sacramento south to San Diego, then north 
through the Central Valley and into San Francisco. Wilson was to tape a public 
affairs television show in San Francisco, then speak to Asian American leaders 
in the city's Chinatown district. While there, he also planned to telephone 
voters on behalf of the state Republican ticket. 
</P>
<P>
 THE SENATE RACE 
</P>
<P>
 * What Happened Tuesday: GOP candidate Mike Huffington held a rally in 
Victorville to protest the desert protection bill signed into law Monday by 
President Clinton and pushed through Congress by Huffington's Democratic 
opponent, Dianne Feinstein. Feinstein received the endorsements of Los Angeles 
city officials at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 * What's Ahead: Huffington will speak to Town Hall in Los Angeles. Feinstein 
is scheduled to appear at events in Orange County and the Inland Empire. 
</P>
<P>
 NOTABLE QUOTES 
</P>
<P>
 "I was shocked to read that you have refused to tell the people of California 
how you would implement Proposition 187 until after the election. Not only is 
this cowardly, it is irresponsible." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Kathleen Brown, in a letter sent to Pete Wilson 
</P>
<P>
 "To accuse people of cowardice is simply name-calling." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Wilson, in a spoken response 
</P>
